messages.message: It's a race condition in the infrastructure. Many celery workers try to write to one redis key which leads to problems at times. Infra is aware of this problem.
It's just good to remind ourselves how our customers might feel when Instabase depicts such behavior :slightly_smiling_face:
got it. is this a relatively new behavior? didn’t notice it until maybe the last deployment, and now i see it every time i run a flow binary :slightly_smiling_face:
It was something that would be really hard to fix on the backend right? We could put in a simple conditional on the front end to only show the total number of pages if it’s >0
